Here's my tips for starting out drawing.
>don't give up
>don't be too hard on yourself
>don't push yourself too hard
>loosen up
>practice by drawing from refs, timed and untimed
>analyzing your mistakes is as important as practice
>draw for yourself
>draw lines, not symbols
>treat tutorials like advice
I started out with a few minutes of timed practice with really low timers. Don't burn yourself out, but don't give up either.
Even something as small as five minutes a day is better than nothing. You're not going to live up to your expectations. After a while, you'll be able to tell what you need practice on.

Oh yeah and maybe fix your hand.
